<date id="FFD51002870AAA1546F9FBAADAA9AE57" box="[228,457,1112,1139]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" value="1938-04-25" valueMax="1938-04-26" valueMin="1938-04-25">April 25–26, 1938</date>
. Cockerell described both sexes of this species, but he did not indicate how many specimens of each sex he used. Apparently, the type series was composed of at least one male and two females, which were found at 
<collectionCode id="ED7AAE07870AAA15448CFB52D98FAE9F" box="[657,751,1184,1210]" country="USA" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/142r-0w94" name="Smithsonian Institution, National Museum of Natural History" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" type="Museum">NMNH</collectionCode>
. The male was chosen as 
<typeStatus id="54D08860870AAA15423AFB6DDFF2AE9C" box="[1063,1170,1183,1209]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">holotype</typeStatus>
. and it was labeled by Cockerell as such. The male 
<typeStatus id="54D08860870AAA154422FB31D9C6AEF8" box="[575,678,1219,1245]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">holotype</typeStatus>
(
